      <h1 class='title'>PENSION LIBERATION: INTERPRETATIO</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 08 July 2004 vol 663 cc184-5GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_184gc' title='Col. 184GC &mdash; HL Deb 08 July 2004 vol 663 c184GC' name='column_184gc' href='#column_184gc' rel='bookmark'>184GC</a>
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_72' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> In this section and sections (<i>Pension liberation: court's power to order restitution</i>), (<i>Pension liberation: restraining orders</i>) and (<i>Pension liberation: repatriation orders</i>)&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_73' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> "pension scheme" means an occupational pension scheme or a personal pension scheme,</li>
        <li> "deposit-taker" has the meaning given by subsections (8A) and (8B) of section 49 of the <a href="/acts/pensions-act-1995">Pensions Act 1995</a> (c. 26), except that, for the purposes of this definition, subsection (8A)(c) of that section has effect with the omission of the words from "or" to the end,</li>
        <li> references to money liberated from a pension scheme are to be read in accordance with subsection (2),</li>
        <li> "liberated member", in relation to money liberated from a pension scheme, means the member of the pension scheme who is referred to in subsection (2)(a), and</li>
        <li> "restraining order" means a restraining order under section (<i>Pension liberation: restraining orders</i>).</li>
        <li> Money is to be taken to have been liberated from a pension scheme if&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_74' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> the money directly or indirectly represents an amount that, in respect of accrued rights of a member of a pension scheme, has been transferred out of the scheme in pursuance of&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_75' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> a relevant statutory provision, or</li>
        <li> a provision of the applicable rules, other than a relevant statutory provision,</li>
        <li> the trustees or managers of the scheme transferred the amount out of the scheme on the basis that a third party ("the liberator") would secure that the amount was used in an authorised way,</li>
        <li> the amount has not been used in an authorised way, and</li>
        <li> the liberator has not secured, and is not likely to secure, that the amount will be used in an authorised way.</li>
        <li> The following are "relevant statutory provisions" for the purposes of subsection (2)&#x2014;</li>
        
        <col>GC 185</col>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_76' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> section 94(1)(a), (aa) or (b) of the <a href="/acts/pension-schemes-act-1993">Pension Schemes Act 1993</a> (c. 48) (right to cash equivalent under Chapter 4 of Part 4 of that Act);</li>
        <li> section 101AB(1)(a) of that Act (right to cash transfer sum under Chapter 5 of Part 4 of that Act);</li>
        <li> section 101F(1) of that Act (right to cash equivalent of pension credit benefit).</li>
        <li> In subsection (2) "authorised way" means&#x2014;</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_77' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <ol>
        <li> where the amount concerned is transferred out of the scheme in pursuance of a provision mentioned in subsection (3)(a), a way specified in subsection (2) or, as the case may be, subsection (3) of section 95 of the <a href="/acts/pension-schemes-act-1993">Pension Schemes Act 1993</a> (c. 48);</li>
        <li> where that amount is transferred out in pursuance of the provision mentioned in subsection (3)(b), a way specified in section 101AE(2) of that Act;</li>
        <li> where that amount is transferred out in pursuance of the provision mentioned in subsection (3)(c), a way specified in subsection (2) or, as the case may be, subsection (3) of section 101F of that Act;</li>
        <li> where that amount is transferred out in pursuance of a provision of the kind mentioned in subsection (2)(a)(ii), a way that is authorised by the applicable rules for amounts transferred out in pursuance of that provision.</li>
        <li> In this section "the applicable rules" has the same meaning as, in the case of the pension scheme concerned, that expression has in section 94 of the <a href="/acts/pension-schemes-act-1993">Pension Schemes Act 1993</a> (c. 48)."</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      
      <q id='S5LV0663P0_20040708_GCR2_78'>
        After Clause 18, insert the following new clause&#x2014;
      </q>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
      </ol>
      
